Untitled

Jason Moggridge

2023-07-28

Information

“The sample size of 60 individuals with SGLT2 inhibitor DKA provides >80% power to uncover a significant association (P<5x10-8) with genetic variants (minor allele frequency 0.20; odds-ratio>5) and DKA, as calculated using the R package, genpwr.”

“Our plan is to match cases N=60 3:1 (or so) thus we will have 180 controls.”

  • Design: Case-control GWAS.

  • Sample size: 60 cases, 180+ controls.

  • Assay: Illumina GSA-24 (~654,027 markers)

  • Assumptions: SGLT2-DKA associated variants are presumed to have a large effect size (OR > 5) and be common (MAF 0.2) in the study population.

  • Alpha: the significance threshold is 0.05 / 1M tests = 5x10^-8

Further Assumptions*

Genetic model: Additive

Replicate the calculation of sample size: 60 cases and 180 controls…

sample_calc <- 
  genpwr::genpwr.calc(
    calc = 'ss',
    model = 'logistic',
    ge.interaction = NULL,
    Power = .8,
    MAF = seq(.05, .5, .01),
    OR = 5,
    Alpha = .05,
    Case.Rate = seq(.01, .5, .01)
  )

sample_calc |> 
    mutate(
    test = str_glue('test = {Test.Model}'),
    true = str_glue('true = {True.Model}'),
  ) |> 
  ggplot(aes(Case.Rate, N_total_at_Alpha_0.05)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = MAF, group = factor(MAF)), 
            alpha = .76) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 60, lty = 2, alpha = .7) +
  geom_vline(xintercept = .25, lty = 2, alpha = .7) +
  scale_y_log10() +
  scale_color_viridis_c() + 
  facet_grid(test ~ true)

So we are 80% powered to detect DKA-associated markers with MAF = 0.2 and OR > 5

sample_sizes <-
  tibble(
    cases = 60,
    controls = 180,
    added_controls = 2 ^ seq(-1, 16, 1) |> round(),
    N_total = cases + controls + added_controls,
    k = (N_total - cases) / cases,
    Case.Rate = cases / N_total
  ) |>
  distinct()

gwas_power <- genpwr::genpwr.calc(
  calc = 'power',
  model = 'logistic',
  ge.interaction = NULL,
  N = sample_sizes$N_total,
  Case.Rate = sample_sizes$Case.Rate,
  MAF = .2,
  OR = c(1.05, 1.25, 2, 5),
  Alpha = 0.05,
  True.Model = c('Dominant', 'Recessive', 'Additive'),
  Test.Model = c('Dominant', 'Recessive', 'Additive', '2df')
) |>
  as_tibble() |> 
  print()

sample_sizes |>
  left_join(
    gwas_power, by = join_by(N_total, Case.Rate)
  ) |>
  mutate(
    test = str_glue('test = {Test.Model}'),
    true = str_glue('true = {True.Model}'),
  ) |> 
  ggplot(aes(
    x = added_controls + 1,
    y = `Power_at_Alpha_0.05`,
    color = as_factor(OR),
  )) +
  geom_point(size = .81) +
  geom_line(aes(group = factor(OR))) +
  facet_grid(test~true) +
  scale_color_viridis_d(
    end = .9, 
    option = 'mako'
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    labels = scales::label_percent()
  ) +
  scale_x_log10() +
  labs(
    x = 'Additional controls (N + 1)',
    y = expression('Power at alpha = 0.05'),
    color = 'OR',
    shape = 'MAF',
    alpha = 'MAF',
    title = 
      'Power to detect associations with 60 cases and 180+ controls',
  ) +
  guides(
    shape = guide_legend('MAF', 
                         override.aes = list(size = 2, linewidth = 1))
  ) +
  theme_classic() +
  theme(
    axis.title.y = ggtext::element_markdown()
  )

dat <- genpwr.calc(
  calc = "power", 
  model = "logistic", 
  ge.interaction = NULL,
  N = 240,
  Case.Rate = 0.25,
  k = NULL,
  MAF = seq(0.05, 0.8, 0.05),
  OR = 10^seq(0.01, 1, 0.01),
  Alpha = 0.05,
  True.Model = c("Dominant", "Recessive", "Additive"),
  Test.Model = c("Dominant", "Recessive", "Additive", "2df")
  ) |> 
  glimpse() |> 
  arrange(MAF) |> 
  mutate(
    test = str_glue('test = {Test.Model}'),
    true = str_glue('true = {True.Model}'),
  )
